race.comment: A good Class 1 although light on numbers. MELANITE (1) resumed with an excellent all-the-way win in the $250k Magic Million Maiden over 1100m at the Gold Coast last start. Good form is already coming out of that race. Beautifully drawn and coming back to 1000m is no knock. Can keep the momentum going. GAMBLER (2) appreciated being ridden close to the speed last time out when runner-up over this trip at Kembla. Very fit and from a good draw he should be prominent for a long way again. FIERCE (3) last raced when a narrow winner on debut over today's distance at Hawkesbury in September. The winner of two recent trials so he looks fully wound up. NOTHING BUT NET (7) struggled over 1200m at Gosford last start and should improve sharply coming back to five furlongs. AETERNUM (6) dominated in a Taree maiden last start and with the light weight can be competitive in this better company.
